<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefbf97a6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4819"><num value="4819">§ 4819.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idefbf97a7-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4819/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary for the Secretary to carry out this chapter, subject to reimbursement from the Board under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s4809/c/3/B/iv">section 4809(c)(3)(B)(iv) of this title</ref>.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idefbf97a8-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4819/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Sums appropriated to carry out this chapter shall not be available for payment of an expense or expenditure incurred by the Board in administering an order.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idefbf97a9-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/198/tXVI/s1630">Pub. L. 99–198, title XVI, § 1630</ref>, <date date="1985-12-23">Dec. 23, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/1621">99 Stat. 1621</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idefc207aa-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idefc207ab-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idefc207ac-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1986-01-01">Jan. 1, 1986</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/198/s1631">section 1631 of Pub. L. 99–198</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s4801">section 4801 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
